data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value: To install binaries, connect a RoboRIO to the PC using USB, and press "Update Binaries" To Connect to the Roborio, put the RoboRIO's Address in the Diagnostic Server Address Box and suffix it with ":1250" The Address of the RoboRIO will be 172.22.11.2 if over USB, and 10.TE.AM.x if over ethernet or WiFi

data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value: This is the Log for HTTP Requests for debugging purposes. Every line will display either a URL or a Json object URL's are sent from the client to the server, with key points of data specified under the "device", "id", "action" parameters Json objects are sent from the server to the client in response to the URL's that the client queries.

data.name: richTextBox3.Text
data.value:
This is the "Easter Egg'd" Tab for testing the deployment procedure overnight. The checkboxes on the left are the tests to make when going through a run. Specify the tests, connect to the RIO over USB, and press Begin Overnight Test to begin. The Tests will loop forever until you press the "Stop Test" button or something goes wrong in a test. Anything that goes wrong will be printed in the display to the left.
NOTE: - If the tests consist of modifying devices or using firmware files, select the device in the device viewer inside "CAN Devices" first.
